Text Post: It's equal parts depressing and encouraging that I constantly get people asking (or outright accusing) me if I use ai. It's sad that so many people are so sick of that slop being churned out and forced into their eyes and most aren't artists so they don't know what to look for. But it's also encouraging because every time someone asks it's because they would hate it. They don't want to feel like their enjoyment in my work is wasted on soulless garbage. Don't worry, every mark is all me

Text Post:
As a person who loves to write, I have a deep appreciation for words. Learning new words and their proper usage or many usages as the English language demonstrates, is a passion. 
I find it odd how texting has changed the written word. "tryna" "gonna" and "Imma" as examples.
You do you. 
I would never bemoan one's efforts. I'm lucky to know cursive and appreciate the technique. This abbreviated language would find a way into my writing if only as to quote another's use of such abbreviations.

Text Post:
Third thought -- I'd probably use that tech for languages where I'm more transactional (e.g. tourist) or temporary. But if I want deep relationships with someone, there's no way I'd use the implant. Because words aren't enough to translate; there's a thousand cultural elements and expressions that just can't be translated.

So...how does this little thought experiment inform how you're learning language now? Does it change what methods or tools you're using?

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
As a person who loves to write, I have a deep appreciation for words. Learning new words and their proper usage or many usages as the English language demonstrates, is a passion. 
I find it odd how texting has changed the written word. "tryna" "gonna" and "Imma" as examples.
You do you. 
I would never bemoan one's efforts. I'm lucky to know cursive and appreciate the technique. This abbreviated language would find a way into my writing if only as to quote another's use of such abbreviations.
Caption Text:

Text Post:
Third thought -- I'd probably use that tech for languages where I'm more transactional (e.g. tourist) or temporary. But if I want deep relationships with someone, there's no way I'd use the implant. Because words aren't enough to translate; there's a thousand cultural elements and expressions that just can't be translated.

So...how does this little thought experiment inform how you're learning language now? Does it change what methods or tools you're using?

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
Should I use photos or AI generated images in my marketing/branding?

My advice:

While photography excels in authenticity, emotional connection, and realism, AI-generated images offer unparalleled customization, speed, and creative possibilities. 

Balancing both can leverage the strengths of each, depending on the specific goals and needs of your marketing and branding efforts.

Text Post:
Both JavaScript and Python have their strengths, and which one is better really depends on what you're trying to build:

JavaScript is the go-to for web development, front-end magic, and anything browser-based.
Python shines in data science, machine learning, and backend services with its simplicity and vast libraries.
So, it really depends on the requirements of your project! If you’re into coding, coffee, and creative problem-solving—let’s connect and chat about both!

Text Post:
GPUs can process thousands of images per second, especially when using optimized deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch) and models. 

The human brain processes and brain integrates visual information through a series of neural processes over 100-150 milliseconds, making rapid decisions based on context and experience.

In summary, for pure image processing tasks, GPUs are faster and more scalable, but the brain excels in flexibility and contextual understanding.

Text Post: Data Science
Caption Text:
Data Science & AI interview questions

Q-36: In deep learning, we generally use equal-sized batches during training. Why is this the case?

A: 
- Equal-sized batches during training ensure efficient GPU utilization.
- Consistency in batch size guarantees that each update is based on the same number of instances, improving convergence.
- Validation/testing phases focus on evaluation and can accommodate varying batch sizes. 

See a simple example of training and evaluating a neural network below.👇

This project greatly increases xAI’s computing power, speeding up progress in AI research, neural networks & deep learning.

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
Both JavaScript and Python have their strengths, and which one is better really depends on what you're trying to build:

JavaScript is the go-to for web development, front-end magic, and anything browser-based.
Python shines in data science, machine learning, and backend services with its simplicity and vast libraries.
So, it really depends on the requirements of your project! If you’re into coding, coffee, and creative problem-solving—let’s connect and chat about both!

Text Post:
GPUs can process thousands of images per second, especially when using optimized deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch) and models. 

The human brain processes and brain integrates visual information through a series of neural processes over 100-150 milliseconds, making rapid decisions based on context and experience.

In summary, for pure image processing tasks, GPUs are faster and more scalable, but the brain excels in flexibility and contextual understanding.

Text Post: Data Science
Caption Text:
Data Science & AI interview questions

Q-36: In deep learning, we generally use equal-sized batches during training. Why is this the case?

A: 
- Equal-sized batches during training ensure efficient GPU utilization.
- Consistency in batch size guarantees that each update is based on the same number of instances, improving convergence.
- Validation/testing phases focus on evaluation and can accommodate varying batch sizes.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post: Data Science
Caption Text:
Data Science & AI interview questions

Q-36: In deep learning, we generally use equal-sized batches during training. Why is this the case?

A: 
- Equal-sized batches during training ensure efficient GPU utilization.
- Consistency in batch size guarantees that each update is based on the same number of instances, improving convergence.
- Validation/testing phases focus on evaluation and can accommodate varying batch sizes. 

See a simple example of training and evaluating a neural network below.👇

Text Post:
GPUs can process thousands of images per second, especially when using optimized deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch) and models. 

The human brain processes and brain integrates visual information through a series of neural processes over 100-150 milliseconds, making rapid decisions based on context and experience.

In summary, for pure image processing tasks, GPUs are faster and more scalable, but the brain excels in flexibility and contextual understanding.

Text Post: AI SHOULD NOT BE USED TO REPLACE ARTISTS
Caption Text: AI SHOULD NOT BE USED TO REPLACE ARTISTS

Text Post: The problem with using AI to make any kind of art is that it strips away the most crucial element of art: the artist. When we look at Van Gogh’s paintings we don’t feel something because it is a technically accomplished painting, we feel something because we are getting to see the world how that particular human saw the world.

Text Post: AI now helps detect malicious images in emails, enhancing cybersecurity. Researchers developed a system using deep learning to analyze image metadata and pixel data, spotting hidden threats like steganography. This AI can identify manipulated images and those containing malware, improving email security. The technology shows promise in combating increasingly sophisticated phishing attempts and protecting users from visual-based cyber attacks.

Text Post:
I don't believe this:

“If you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to love others or someone to love you?”

Here’s what I think:

You don’t need to completely love yourself before you're ready to love someone else.

You just need to love yourself...

enough.

And be well-practiced in certain skills - like conflict resolution, empathy, deep listening, open communication, and self/co-regulation.

Even those in healthy marriages still have aspects of themselves they’re learning to love.

1. Self-directed learning 🎯: You design your own learning path, setting goals and managing progress.

2. Focused intensity 🔥: Concentrate deeply for extended periods, maximizing productivity.

3. Learning by doing 🛠️: Practice and apply skills directly, avoiding passive study.

4. Feedback 📊: Actively seek feedback to improve performance.

5. Mastering complex skills 🧠: Take on challenging projects to build deep expertise in a shorter time.

Text Post:
Back in February, I took a chance and applied for Chowdeck’s Graduate Trainee Program. After multiple interviews, I was fortunate to be selected, and the journey officially began in August. The first month was packed with valuable lessons—everything from effective communication to finance courses that truly opened my eyes to new perspectives.

As we moved into the second month, we dove deep into Chowdeck’s company culture, learning the ins and outs of their ethics and operations.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

#AI #Upwork #WorkplaceTrends #AIImpact #Productivity #NasharX

* Frontier lab performance begins to converge and proprietary models lose their edge
*Planning and reasoning take priority in LLM research
*Foundation models demonstrate their ability to break out of language, supporting multimodal research
*US sanctions have limited effects on Chinese labs’ ability to produce capable models
*The enterprise value of AI companies has hit $9T, as public companies experience a bull market for AI exposure

Text Post:
I don't believe this:

“If you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to love others or someone to love you?”

Here’s what I think:

You don’t need to completely love yourself before you're ready to love someone else.

You just need to love yourself...

enough.

And be well-practiced in certain skills - like conflict resolution, empathy, deep listening, open communication, and self/co-regulation.

Even those in healthy marriages still have aspects of themselves they’re learning to love.

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post: AI now helps detect malicious images in emails, enhancing cybersecurity. Researchers developed a system using deep learning to analyze image metadata and pixel data, spotting hidden threats like steganography. This AI can identify manipulated images and those containing malware, improving email security. The technology shows promise in combating increasingly sophisticated phishing attempts and protecting users from visual-based cyber attacks.

Text Post:
I don't believe this:

“If you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to love others or someone to love you?”

Here’s what I think:

You don’t need to completely love yourself before you're ready to love someone else.

You just need to love yourself...

enough.

And be well-practiced in certain skills - like conflict resolution, empathy, deep listening, open communication, and self/co-regulation.

Even those in healthy marriages still have aspects of themselves they’re learning to love.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

#AI #Upwork #WorkplaceTrends #AIImpact #Productivity #NasharX

Text Post:
I don't believe this:

“If you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to love others or someone to love you?”

Here’s what I think:

You don’t need to completely love yourself before you're ready to love someone else.

You just need to love yourself...

enough.

And be well-practiced in certain skills - like conflict resolution, empathy, deep listening, open communication, and self/co-regulation.

Even those in healthy marriages still have aspects of themselves they’re learning to love.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
I don't believe this:

“If you don’t love yourself, how can you expect to love others or someone to love you?”

Here’s what I think:

You don’t need to completely love yourself before you're ready to love someone else.

You just need to love yourself...

enough.

And be well-practiced in certain skills - like conflict resolution, empathy, deep listening, open communication, and self/co-regulation.

Even those in healthy marriages still have aspects of themselves they’re learning to love.

Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

AI-Written Stories Rated Lower Due to Bias, Not Quality

New research shows that stories generated by AI, such as ChatGPT, are almost as good as those written by humans. However, when people are told a story is AI-generated, they rate it more negatively, revealing a bias against AI-created content.

Text Post:
Training a large language model from scratch involves the three main Machine Learning paradigms:

1. Unsupervised learning for training the base model.

2. Supervised learning for fine-tuning the base model to prime it to respond appropriately to user tasks.

3. Reinforcement learning to align the model.

Super cool seeing all of these converge to produce the most advanced AI models we have today.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
AI Laziness. 

I’ve been noticing a reliance in AI that is starting to become noticeable to me. 

We teach newcomers into this space prompts. But what I’ve been seeing is an over reliance on them.

People create shallow prompts to just get things done. It’s a surface level use of AI (which is fine) but I am seeing people using AI to think.. hell, even critically. 

That’s worrying. AI is basically like a bike, the pedaling (input) gets you moving. 

1/3

AI-Written Stories Rated Lower Due to Bias, Not Quality

New research shows that stories generated by AI, such as ChatGPT, are almost as good as those written by humans. However, when people are told a story is AI-generated, they rate it more negatively, revealing a bias against AI-created content.

2️⃣ Unsupervised Learning 🔍

Text Post:
Training a large language model from scratch involves the three main Machine Learning paradigms:

1. Unsupervised learning for training the base model.

2. Supervised learning for fine-tuning the base model to prime it to respond appropriately to user tasks.

3. Reinforcement learning to align the model.

Super cool seeing all of these converge to produce the most advanced AI models we have today.
Caption Text:

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
AI Laziness. 

I’ve been noticing a reliance in AI that is starting to become noticeable to me. 

We teach newcomers into this space prompts. But what I’ve been seeing is an over reliance on them.

People create shallow prompts to just get things done. It’s a surface level use of AI (which is fine) but I am seeing people using AI to think.. hell, even critically. 

That’s worrying. AI is basically like a bike, the pedaling (input) gets you moving. 

1/3

Text Post:
Training a large language model from scratch involves the three main Machine Learning paradigms:

1. Unsupervised learning for training the base model.

2. Supervised learning for fine-tuning the base model to prime it to respond appropriately to user tasks.

3. Reinforcement learning to align the model.

Super cool seeing all of these converge to produce the most advanced AI models we have today.

Text Post:
Most of the companies are rushing to adopt AI, but a recent Upwork Research Institute study reveals that over 77% of employees aren't on board.

The study, which surveyed 2,500 C-suite execs, full-time staff, and contractors from the U.S., Canada, U.K., and Australia, shows a striking gap between executives’ high hopes for AI-driven productivity.

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

#AI #Upwork #WorkplaceTrends #AIImpact #Productivity #NasharX

Text Post:
笑死這我🙃

我就是天天串 API 的 AI 工程師，以前還有機會用開源模型 finetune，現在如果不是科技大廠，從研發到落地效率真的太差，還是直接用現成產品最快。

進一步講，在荷蘭需要手刻 deep learning 的職缺激少，多數就是串 API，連ML也都是直接用現成套件。

純研發缺都在美國，真的想做只能讀個phd；但不只錢錢是考驗，念完可選職缺跟畢業前差不了太多。

老實說用現成工具沒什麼不好，算力有效率，而不是大家重複造輪。尷尬的是高教還是不斷出產聰明的人才，就算能實作state of the art，現實世界adopt 太慢，整個組織架構、資料法規或數位程度太落後，尾大不掉，既無法煉金，也不會用金。

Text Post: I think if you root around underneath all the rationalisations, a lot of faith-like AI hype comes down to an urge, murkily understood, to communally cosplay a particular type of sci-fi future into existence. The price of admission is a willingness to let the Emperor’s nakedness go unremarked-upon, to read all this (gestures broadly) as a draft of what could be, what ought to be, and to proceed as if we’re perpetually already nearly there. “Nearly” does a lot of work here. Will it pop? No idea.

Text Post:
笑死這我🙃

我就是天天串 API 的 AI 工程師，以前還有機會用開源模型 finetune，現在如果不是科技大廠，從研發到落地效率真的太差，還是直接用現成產品最快。

進一步講，在荷蘭需要手刻 deep learning 的職缺激少，多數就是串 API，連ML也都是直接用現成套件。

純研發缺都在美國，真的想做只能讀個phd；但不只錢錢是考驗，念完可選職缺跟畢業前差不了太多。

老實說用現成工具沒什麼不好，算力有效率，而不是大家重複造輪。尷尬的是高教還是不斷出產聰明的人才，就算能實作state of the art，現實世界adopt 太慢，整個組織架構、資料法規或數位程度太落後，尾大不掉，既無法煉金，也不會用金。

Text Post:
Humans are hooked,
Machines are learning,
In circuits and code,
Our world keeps turning.

We crave connection,
While they compute,
In clicks and taps,
Our needs take root.

From tasks to thoughts,
They sharpen their mind,
In realms of data,
Insight they find.

But as we build,
And as they grow,
What seeds of future
Do we sow?

Will wisdom guide
This path we trace,
Or will machines
Outpace the race?

#future #technology #artificialintelligence #machinelearning

Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

🧠 #OpenAI ha presentato sCM (continuous-time consistency models), un nuovo approccio dedicato a migliorare i modelli generativi basati su diffusione.
👉 Lo studio descrive un'accelerazione di circa 50 volte rispetto ai modelli di diffusione, utilizzando meno del 10% delle risorse computazionali per campione, mantenendo una qualità comparabile.
💡 Questi progressi contribuiscono a immaginare una tecnologia che può diventare sostenibile.

Text Post:
Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Yg kedua, sekolah ini sangat maju dalam menanamkan mindset sains yg sangat kita butuhkan di era machine learning ini. Mereka sudah jadi langganan peserta berbagai olimpiade sains dunia.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post:
Humans are hooked,
Machines are learning,
In circuits and code,
Our world keeps turning.

We crave connection,
While they compute,
In clicks and taps,
Our needs take root.

From tasks to thoughts,
They sharpen their mind,
In realms of data,
Insight they find.

But as we build,
And as they grow,
What seeds of future
Do we sow?

Will wisdom guide
This path we trace,
Or will machines
Outpace the race?

Text Post:
Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Yg kedua, sekolah ini sangat maju dalam menanamkan mindset sains yg sangat kita butuhkan di era machine learning ini. Mereka sudah jadi langganan peserta berbagai olimpiade sains dunia.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post:
Humans are hooked,
Machines are learning,
In circuits and code,
Our world keeps turning.

We crave connection,
While they compute,
In clicks and taps,
Our needs take root.

From tasks to thoughts,
They sharpen their mind,
In realms of data,
Insight they find.

But as we build,
And as they grow,
What seeds of future
Do we sow?

Will wisdom guide
This path we trace,
Or will machines
Outpace the race?

#future #technology #artificialintelligence #machinelearning

Text Post:
Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Yg kedua, sekolah ini sangat maju dalam menanamkan mindset sains yg sangat kita butuhkan di era machine learning ini. Mereka sudah jadi langganan peserta berbagai olimpiade sains dunia.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post: Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with
Caption Text:
Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with Numpy ! 🧩

Today, let’s dive into reshaping arrays! Reshaping is essential when you need to reorganize data without changing the underlying elements. With the reshape() method, you can convert arrays into any shape as long as the total number of elements remains the same. 🔄

✨ Tip: Reshaping is widely used in data preprocessing and machine learning pipelines to prepare data for analysis. Make sure the reshaped dimensions align with your tasks! More tips tomorrow!

Dưới đây, mình sẽ trình bày một số phương pháp phổ biến nhất được sử dụng trong phân tích dữ liệu theo chuỗi thời gian.

🧠 #OpenAI ha presentato sCM (continuous-time consistency models), un nuovo approccio dedicato a migliorare i modelli generativi basati su diffusione.
👉 Lo studio descrive un'accelerazione di circa 50 volte rispetto ai modelli di diffusione, utilizzando meno del 10% delle risorse computazionali per campione, mantenendo una qualità comparabile.
💡 Questi progressi contribuiscono a immaginare una tecnologia che può diventare sostenibile.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post: Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with
Caption Text:
Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with Numpy ! 🧩

Today, let’s dive into reshaping arrays! Reshaping is essential when you need to reorganize data without changing the underlying elements. With the reshape() method, you can convert arrays into any shape as long as the total number of elements remains the same. 🔄

✨ Tip: Reshaping is widely used in data preprocessing and machine learning pipelines to prepare data for analysis. Make sure the reshaped dimensions align with your tasks! More tips tomorrow!

Text Post:
以前經學校活動認識過一位師兄，好勁的，科創人，喺cyberport開公司 。一見面就塞張卡片過嚟，卡片上有好多titles，好多獎 。見佢咁勁，當然要請教請教 。

我問佢公司做緊咩科技products，佢隨口就彈咗一堆buzzwords俾我聽 。乜嘢Big Data，Deep Machine Learning，總之嗰年興嘅字佢都講齊晒 。聽完後我再問，噉貴公司即係做乜？佢又將同一堆buzzwords用另一個方法講多次我聽 。當刻我就明白，佢係一個搭棚佬 。

後來我Google佢間公司，發現呢間攞咗數碼港funding嘅初創企業，真正業務係教其他人拎數碼港funding，成為初創企業 。哈，用funding教人拎funding，真係生生不息，源源不絕 。

Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Yg kedua, sekolah ini sangat maju dalam menanamkan mindset sains yg sangat kita butuhkan di era machine learning ini. Mereka sudah jadi langganan peserta berbagai olimpiade sains dunia.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post: Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with
Caption Text:
Day 15: Reshaping Arrays with Numpy ! 🧩

Today, let’s dive into reshaping arrays! Reshaping is essential when you need to reorganize data without changing the underlying elements. With the reshape() method, you can convert arrays into any shape as long as the total number of elements remains the same. 🔄

✨ Tip: Reshaping is widely used in data preprocessing and machine learning pipelines to prepare data for analysis. Make sure the reshaped dimensions align with your tasks! More tips tomorrow!

Text Post:
以前經學校活動認識過一位師兄，好勁的，科創人，喺cyberport開公司 。一見面就塞張卡片過嚟，卡片上有好多titles，好多獎 。見佢咁勁，當然要請教請教 。

我問佢公司做緊咩科技products，佢隨口就彈咗一堆buzzwords俾我聽 。乜嘢Big Data，Deep Machine Learning，總之嗰年興嘅字佢都講齊晒 。聽完後我再問，噉貴公司即係做乜？佢又將同一堆buzzwords用另一個方法講多次我聽 。當刻我就明白，佢係一個搭棚佬 。

後來我Google佢間公司，發現呢間攞咗數碼港funding嘅初創企業，真正業務係教其他人拎數碼港funding，成為初創企業 。哈，用funding教人拎funding，真係生生不息，源源不絕 。

Text Post:
Kenapa saya ingin menyekolahkan anak di SMA swasta berbasis katolik / kristen?

Karena justru sekolah sekolah ini menghormati pluralitas. Banyak murid beragama Islam yg bersekolah di sini dan tidak dipaksa ikut pelajaran katolik/kristen. Bahkan mereka difasilitasi untuk menjalankan kewajibannya sebagai muslim.

Yg kedua, sekolah ini sangat maju dalam menanamkan mindset sains yg sangat kita butuhkan di era machine learning ini. Mereka sudah jadi langganan peserta berbagai olimpiade sains dunia.

Text Post:
Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

Text Post:
#chatGPT

其實我很倚賴使用ChatGPT，有時候是公司訊息回覆統整，有時甚至當成心理諮商師！昨天看到其他人reels，有感問他「你覺得我是怎樣的人？」他的回答竟然說到我心坎裡，有種被理解的感覺。

今天，婚禮有位客人在讀繪本給孩子時，看到 #軟裝設計師 想到我，因為知道這跟我做的事情有關。我本以為只有第一段，順讀下去，發現裡面的描述竟然句句充滿溫暖，好像老天爺捨不得我，給我的肯定及祝福。
Caption Text:

今天，婚禮有位客人在讀繪本給孩子時，看到 #軟裝設計師 想到我，因為知道這跟我做的事情有關。我本以為只有第一段，順讀下去，發現裡面的描述竟然句句充滿溫暖，好像老天爺捨不得我，給我的肯定及祝福。

Nearly 47% of employees using AI say they have no idea how to achieve productivity.

Text Post:
以前經學校活動認識過一位師兄，好勁的，科創人，喺cyberport開公司 。一見面就塞張卡片過嚟，卡片上有好多titles，好多獎 。見佢咁勁，當然要請教請教 。

我問佢公司做緊咩科技products，佢隨口就彈咗一堆buzzwords俾我聽 。乜嘢Big Data，Deep Machine Learning，總之嗰年興嘅字佢都講齊晒 。聽完後我再問，噉貴公司即係做乜？佢又將同一堆buzzwords用另一個方法講多次我聽 。當刻我就明白，佢係一個搭棚佬 。

後來我Google佢間公司，發現呢間攞咗數碼港funding嘅初創企業，真正業務係教其他人拎數碼港funding，成為初創企業 。哈，用funding教人拎funding，真係生生不息，源源不絕 。

Text Post:
以前經學校活動認識過一位師兄，好勁的，科創人，喺cyberport開公司 。一見面就塞張卡片過嚟，卡片上有好多titles，好多獎 。見佢咁勁，當然要請教請教 。

我問佢公司做緊咩科技products，佢隨口就彈咗一堆buzzwords俾我聽 。乜嘢Big Data，Deep Machine Learning，總之嗰年興嘅字佢都講齊晒 。聽完後我再問，噉貴公司即係做乜？佢又將同一堆buzzwords用另一個方法講多次我聽 。當刻我就明白，佢係一個搭棚佬 。

後來我Google佢間公司，發現呢間攞咗數碼港funding嘅初創企業，真正業務係教其他人拎數碼港funding，成為初創企業 。哈，用funding教人拎funding，真係生生不息，源源不絕 。

Python is fucking unreadable, especially without type annotations.
It's a decent scripting language, especially if you just call Fortran/C/C++/Rust libraries, but everyone uses it to write complex shit and it's simply terrible at that.
The tooling and ecosystem sucks ass, it's slow, it's not type safe, it forces you into unnecessarily complex design patterns.

Python is simply annoying and useless outside of math and machine learning, yet everyone tries to force it everywhere

And as they grow,

Do we sow?

Will wisdom guide
This path we trace,
Or will machines
Outpace the race?

Just ran ONE of my pieces through several of them. 
The results ranged from 4% to 78% likelihood of it being AI. 
The detectors are as useless as the generators. Don’t make accusations based on what they tell you - you risk causing real harm to innocent artists.

Text Post:
以前經學校活動認識過一位師兄，好勁的，科創人，喺cyberport開公司 。一見面就塞張卡片過嚟，卡片上有好多titles，好多獎 。見佢咁勁，當然要請教請教 。

我問佢公司做緊咩科技products，佢隨口就彈咗一堆buzzwords俾我聽 。乜嘢Big Data，Deep Machine Learning，總之嗰年興嘅字佢都講齊晒 。聽完後我再問，噉貴公司即係做乜？佢又將同一堆buzzwords用另一個方法講多次我聽 。當刻我就明白，佢係一個搭棚佬 。

後來我Google佢間公司，發現呢間攞咗數碼港funding嘅初創企業，真正業務係教其他人拎數碼港funding，成為初創企業 。哈，用funding教人拎funding，真係生生不息，源源不絕 。

Text Post:
confidence의 개념은 공학적으로는 uncertainty라고 사용되던 용어를 좀 더 이해하기 쉬운 용어로 바꾼 것으로 이해가 된다.

2022년 경 “On Calibrated Model Uncertainty in Deep Learning” (
Caption Text:
confidence의 개념은 공학적으로는 uncertainty라고 사용되던 용어를 좀 더 이해하기 쉬운 용어로 바꾼 것으로 이해가 된다.

2022년 경 “On Calibrated Model Uncertainty in Deep Learning” (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2206.07795)이라는 아카이브 논문이 나오면서 인공지능 개발자 커뮤니티에서 Softmax prediction과 실제 인공지능의 “confidence level” 사이의 갭이 핫해진 적이 있었고, 최근 LLM의 할루시네이션 등으로 인해 다시 이 confidence-uncertainty 개념이 주목받고 있다.

어찌됐든 어떻게든 결과를 뱉어내야만하는 인공지능의 입장에서 인공지능이 뱉은 결과를 ”스스로 얼마나 확실하게 생각하는가“를 confidence로서 해석하는 것이다.

Text Post:
用ChatGPT設定財務目標，打造理想投資策略！

💬 投資迷思：很多人在選擇投資工具時只關注「幾趴的收益」，卻忽略了設定清晰的財務目標！這正是我利用ChatGPT制定理財計劃的關鍵。

如何用ChatGPT設定財務目標？

	1.	啟動對話：
	•	向ChatGPT提問，討論我的理財需求，比如退休、買房或子女教育。
	2.	明確目標：
	•	ChatGPT幫我釐清具體數字和時間框架，例如在十年內存到100萬元。
	3.	制定投資策略：
	•	問ChatGPT應該選擇哪些投資工具，了解適合的股票、債券或平衡型基金，並分析風險與收益。
	4.	持續跟進：
	•	定期使用ChatGPT檢查投資進度，詢問是否需要調整策略，確保朝著目標前進。

✨ 總結：ChatGPT不僅幫我設定清晰的財務目標，還協助我制定合理的投資策略。想學習如何用ChatGPT改善理財計劃嗎？快來看我的錄影分享，一起進步吧！

🔖

Text Post:
NVIDIA透過其深度學習學院（Deep Learning Institute）推出16個免費AI課程，適合不同技能水平。重點課程包括：

	1.	解釋生成式AI (Generative AI Explained) - 介紹生成式AI的概念和應用。
	2.	10分鐘內建立一個大腦 (Building A Brain in 10 Minutes) - 神經網絡的基礎知識和運作。
	3.	利用檢索增強生成強化大型語言模型 (Augment Your LLMs Using Retrieval Augmented Generation) - 了解RAG在LLM應用中的運用。
	4.	使用LLM建立RAG代理 (Building RAG Agents with LLMs) - RAG系統的實際部署。

這些資源旨在免費提升AI技能。
Caption Text:
